pageContext.claim: “We're taking very special care of our nursing homes and our seniors, other than me. Other than me. Nobody wants to take care of me. But other than me, we're taking care of our seniors.”
pageContext.analysis: One-third of all U.S. coronavirus deaths are from either nursing home residents or staff, according to a New York Times report. As for Trump not being cared for, this is a stretch as he is the President of the United States with several personal assistants, drivers, doctors, chefs, and valets.
